body_html: @lcxywfe Thanks for sharing the model. The reason that you didn't get identical results for the same input is because the tensor shape for input and output needs to be identical here. You can feed data separately into the tflite model, i.e. model.set_tensor(input_details[0]['index'], data[0]) and model.set_tensor(input_details[0]['index'], data[1]), then you will get identical results.

body: @lcxywfe Thanks for sharing the model. The reason that you didn't get identical results for the same input is because the tensor shape for input and output needs to be identical here. You can feed `data` separately into the tflite model, i.e. `model.set_tensor(input_details[0]['index'], data[0])` and `model.set_tensor(input_details[0]['index'], data[1])`, then you will get identical results.
